TY  - JOUR
T1  - Contours in Social Change: Elemental Graphics and a Surrogate Variable for Gamma Change
AU  - Golembiewski, Robert T.
Y1  - 1986/07/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4306218
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1986.4306218
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 550
EP  - 566
VL  - 11
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article illustrates the plural concept of change--alpha, beta, and gamma varieties. Socio-political and technical perspectives are employed to reinforce the significance of the concept. In addition, an analysis of a surface with cusp-like properties (a) helps visualize the three types of change; (b) elaborates the interpretive problems; and (c) suggests how the concept can have the inadvertent effect of contributing to a pessimistic view of research and intervention. Finally, a phase model of burn-out seeks to ameliorate this pessimism.
AB  - This article illustrates the plural concept of change--alpha, beta, and gamma varieties. Socio-political and technical perspectives are employed to reinforce the significance of the concept. In addition, an analysis of a surface with cusp-like properties (a) helps visualize the three types of change; (b) elaborates the interpretive problems; and (c) suggests how the concept can have the inadvertent effect of contributing to a pessimistic view of research and intervention. Finally, a phase model of burn-out seeks to ameliorate this pessimism.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1986.4306218
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1986.4306218
Y2  - 2026/04/24
